| Process                         | Thread                                                  |
| ------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------- |
| A process is a running program. | A thread is a small unit of execution inside a process. |
| Has its own memory.             | Shares memory with other threads in the same process.   |
| Creation is slower.             | Creation is faster.                                     |
| Uses more system resources.     | Uses fewer system resources.                            |
| Communication is slower.        | Communication is faster.                                |
| Can contain multiple threads.   | Exists inside a process.                                |
* Why is a Thread Faster than a Process?
A thread is faster because it shares the memory and resources of its process.

what is conqeence?
Concurrency means multiple tasks make progress during the same period of time.

The tasks may not run at the exact same instant, but the CPU switches between them quickly, giving the appearance that they are running together.

Example

📚 While studying, you:

Read notes
Write important points
Solve problems

You switch between these tasks. This is concurrency.

what is parallesium?
Parallelism means executing multiple tasks at the exact same time using multiple CPU cores or processors.

Example

Imagine 2 people working together:

👩 Person 1 → Washing clothes
👨 Person 2 → Cooking food

Both tasks happen simultaneously. This is parallelism.

Computer Example

If a computer has multiple CPU cores:

Core 1 calculates Task A
Core 2 calculates Task B

Both tasks run at the same time.

Parallelism vs Concurrency
Concurrency	Parallelism
Tasks make progress together	Tasks run simultaneously
Can use one CPU core	Usually requires multiple CPU cores
Tasks are switched rapidly	Tasks execute at the same time
Interview Definition

Parallelism is the execution of multiple tasks simultaneously using multiple processors or CPU cores to increase performance and speed.

Simple Memory Trick
Concurrency = Taking turns on tasks.
Parallelism = Doing tasks at the same time. 

# arallelism Using CPU

A CPU can have multiple cores.

Single-core CPU → Executes one task at a time (uses concurrency by switching tasks).
Multi-core CPU → Executes multiple tasks at the same time (parallelism).
Example
Single-Core CPU (Concurrency)
Task A → Task B → Task A → Task B

The CPU switches between tasks very quickly.

Dual-Core CPU (Parallelism)
Core 1 → Task A
Core 2 → Task B

Both tasks run simultaneously.

Real-Life Example

🖥️ 4-Core CPU

Core 1 → Chrome
Core 2 → VS Code
Core 3 → Music Player
Core 4 → Calculator

All can run at the same time.

